<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Cave1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Cave,</orth> subst., 1) cavern, habitation in the earth: <bibl n="shak. ven 830" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 830</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.3.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. V, 3, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 1.3.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 3, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.7.197" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 7, 197</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.3.146" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 146</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.4.202" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 202</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 4.1.52" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. IV, 1, 52</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 2.4.124" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 4, 124</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.2.179" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 179</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.2.74" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 2, 74</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 5.1.122" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. V, 1, 122</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 5.1.122" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. V, 1, 122</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tim 5.2.10" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.2.45" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 2, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.356" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. V, 2, 356</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.3.38" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 3, 38</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.6.83" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 6, 83</bibl> etc. <emph>grim c. of death</emph> (viz night) <bibl n="shak. luc 769" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 769</bibl>. <cit><quote>fall into the blind c. of eternal night,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 5.3.62" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 V, 3, 62</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>lean-faced Envy in her loathsome c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.315" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 315</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>which way shall I find Revenge's c.?</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 3.1.271" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. III, 1, 271</bibl></cit>. (cf. <emph>cave-keeping,</emph> and <cit><quote>cell). cursed the gentle gusts and he that loosed them from their brazen --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.89" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 89</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the c. where Echo lies,</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 2.2.162" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 2, 162</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) any hollow place: <emph>these lovely --s, these round enchanting pits</emph> (viz dimples) <bibl n="shak. ven 247" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 247</bibl>. <cit><quote>as the snail shrinks backward in his shelly c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 247" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 247</bibl></cit>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>